  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IEdge<G extends IGraph<G,E,N>,E extends IEdge<G,E,N>,N extends INode<G,E,N>>
    IEdge is an abstract interface to a common directed edge.
    IGraph<G extends IGraph<G,E,N>,E extends IEdge<G,E,N>,N extends INode<G,E,N>>
    IGraph is an abstract interface to a common graph.
    IGraphListener<G extends IGraph<G,E,N>,E extends IEdge<G,E,N>,N extends INode<G,E,N>>
    A class can implement this interface to be informed about changes to a graph.
    INode<G extends IGraph<G,E,N>,E extends IEdge<G,E,N>,N extends INode<G,E,N>>
    INode is an abstract interface to a common node.

    Class Description
    AbstractGraph<G extends IGraph<G,E,N>,E extends IEdge<G,E,N>,N extends INode<G,E,N>>

    CollectionToUnmodifiableSetAdapter<E>
    Given a collection which really behaves like a set (read: has no duplicate entries), implement a read-only set.

    Represents an edge of type E in a graph of type G with nodes of type N having a id of the source node and target node.
    EdgeKey
    An EdgeKey is used to store and find edges by it's primary key: ids of the source node and target node.

    PetriNetOrTransitionSystem
    A class that stores either a Petri net or a labeled transition system.
    SoftMap<K,V>
    A soft reference to a map.
    StructuralExtensionRemover<G extends IGraph<G,E,N>,E extends IEdge<G,E,N>,N extends INode<G,E,N>>
